<br>
When I was a little ogre (1 to +20) and had few people to play with me I found myself soloing.  While soloing I valued killing the mob faster and taking the least amount of damage.  Here's what I valued the stats at:<br>
<br>
1 AC was worth 4str<br>
1 Str was worth 2hp<br>
<br>
Well as I grew (30 to now) and learned about group dynamics I found my role in groups to be primarily the meatshield and hold the aggro and secondarily as the damage dealer.  Another thing i discovered is that 1sta is worth a few hp.  So now the values are:<br>
<br>
1ac is worth 6str.<br>
1Str is worth 2sta.<br>
<br>
What's got me wondering now is the role of the warrior in a pickup group / raid.  I value aggro the most and I know the harder &amp; faster I hit the more aggro I get, thus I don't have to go running off after a mob to keep him from taking my wizzie down for nuking to early.  The meatshield bit is also important because it saves my healers mana spent on keeping me alive.  There's also the damage dealing bit, I'm not a nuker but with a good chanter haste I can go to town and do my share of damage on the mob but I'm no longer the only one dealing damage.  So where is the fine line is there a particluar train of thought on the matter?  Is Str all that, or should I focus on the ac/hp? <br>
<br>
<br>
